Loans to the  agriculture sector  in
 India  may reach 5.2 trillion rupees in the year that began on
April 1, Prakash Bakshi, chairman of the National Bank for
Agriculture and Rural Development said. That will be more than
the 4.75 trillion rupees targeted in the budget for this fiscal
year, he told reporters in  New Delhi  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
